CAPE TOWN - The publication of the new Mining Charter has again been postponed.Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says it will now be gazetted in the next few weeks.Earlier this year, the department said it would publish the redrafted charter at the end of March.READ: Zwane calls on investors to engage with Mining CharterThe document is meant to provide a guideline for the transformation in the industry, including improving the socio-economic conditions of workers.The new draft was first published last year but industry and government departments raised several objections.The Chamber of Mines has threatened legal action if government implements proposed new levies and black ownership targets.eNCA